'''Aglay''' (s Teglizit: Ellipse) d [[tameknut]] isebṭen i d-iteggen s uylan-a: tanafa n tiddi n yal agaz deg tmeknut-a ɣef sin n wagazen ibedden s agensu-ines (ttwasemman [[adik (tusnakt)|idiken]]) ittɣamay ibedd.<ref>[http://www.mathematik.tu-darmstadt.de/~ehartmann/circlegeom.pdf E. Hartmann: Lecture Note ''''Planar Circle Geometries'''', an Introduction to Möbius-, Laguerre- and Minkowski Planes, p. 55] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171215030059/http://www.mathematik.tu-darmstadt.de/~ehartmann/circlegeom.pdf |date=15 dujamber 2017}}</ref>

[[adik (tusnakt)|idiken]] d agazen F1 d F2 deg telɣa. 

Ihi yezmer ad yili usuneɣ n uglay s weɣris yettusbedden seg ijufaṛ-is deg sin n wagazen F1 d F2, d usuneɣ n uglay fell-asen s yimru seg wagaz X. 
[[Tugna:Cone 3d.png|thumb|270px|Talɣa2: [[Akawsar (tanzeggit)|Akaswar]] uwnis amaɣud (azelmaṭ) de wayed imal (ayeffus), ma d azadur-is issiliɣ-d aglay.|amlellay=|ayeffus]]
Aglay daɣen d yiwet n telmest n [[akaswaran|ikaswaranen]], mi ara ad tettwagzam [[uzmig (tanzeggit)|ukaswar]] s weswir imalen deg ugellus n ukaswar ad nessuffeɣ aglay.

